If you're going with that approach, and we know `ModuleCheck()` is always going to have a check number, I think you can run with this but go one step further:

```csharp
private static int _checkNumber = 0; // 👈 implied by Zach's suggestion

                                      // 👇 Automatically bump the number
public static string ModuleCheck() => $"{_checkNumber++}. Checking Modules Needed so the Tracer Loads:";

// Call this 👇 between "stages" to reset the check counts
public static void ResetChecks() => _checkNumber = 0;
```

This feels like best of all worlds to me :)

